# Design fine-tuning (LocalPro)

When polishing or adjusting **visual design**, follow this project’s system instead of inventing new palettes or spacing scales.

## Tokens and sources

- **Colors:** Prefer Tailwind `primary` / `brand` / `surface` and `slate-*` for neutrals. Align with `tailwind.config.ts` and CSS variables in `src/app/globals.css`.
- **Typography:** `font-sans` is Inter (Next font). Headings use `font-semibold` / `font-extrabold` and `tracking-tight` where pages already do.
- **Layout width:** Public/marketing content uses `max-w-site` (1200px) and horizontal padding `px-4 sm:px-6`.

## Public / legal / policy pages (reference pattern)

Match pages that use `PublicHeader` + `PublicFooter`:

- **Page root:** `min-h-screen bg-white` (or `bg-surface` if the rest of the tree already uses app shell colors).
- **Hero:** `bg-gradient-to-br from-white via-brand-50/30 to-primary-50/50` with inner grid `mx-auto max-w-site gap-10 px-4 py-14 sm:px-6 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_360px]`.
- **Eyebrow:** `text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-brand-700`.
- **Hero title:** `text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-[#0a2540] sm:text-5xl`.
- **Hero body:** `text-base leading-7 text-slate-600` with optional `max-w-xl`.
- **Two-column body:** `lg:grid-cols-[260px_minmax(0,1fr)]`, sticky TOC `lg:sticky lg:top-24`, TOC card `rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-card`.

## Components and interactions

- Reuse `@/components/ui/*` and global classes from `globals.css` (`.card`, `.btn-primary`, `.btn-secondary`, `.input`, `.badge`) when they fit before adding new utility stacks.
- **Dark mode:** Use `next-themes` (`class` strategy). Pair light styles with `dark:` variants using existing slate/card/border patterns in `globals.css`.
- **Motion:** Prefer existing animation utilities (`animate-fade-in`, `animate-reveal-up`, `reveal-stagger`) from `globals.css` over ad-hoc keyframes.

## Fine-tuning discipline

- Mirror **neighboring sections** in the same file for spacing, border radius, and type scale.
- Prefer **semantic contrast** (`text-slate-600` body vs `text-[#0a2540]` headings) over low-contrast gray-on-gray.
- Do **not** introduce arbitrary hex colors or new spacing scales unless extending `tailwind.config.ts` for the whole product.
